{"lemma":"ثَعْلَبٌ","slug":"ثَعْلَبٌ","root":"ث.ع.ل.ب","root_slug":"ث-ع-ل-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ث-ع-ل-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4453"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AB%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fox (Vulpes vulpes)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"jackal (Canis aureus)","tags":["dialectal","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a cunning or deceitful person","tags":["figuratively"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ṯaʕlab- (“fox”). Cognate with Akkadian 𒈜𒀀 (šēlebum) and Hebrew שׁוּעָל (šuʿɔl)."},"ipa":["/θaʕ.lab/","/ˈθəʕ.ləb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4453","headword_ar":"ثَعْلَبٌ","root":"vElb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fox; canis vulpes"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.: but in the dial. of Egypt, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jackal; canis aureus"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.: the former animal being there called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw AlHuSayoni","text_ar":"اَبُو الحُصَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as it often is by the Arabs of other countries:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain beast of prey;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaEolabN *akarN","text_ar":"ثَعْلَبٌ ذَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaEolabN","text_ar":"ثَعْلَبٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unovaY","text_ar":"اُنْثَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but if one would designate the male by a single word applying to it only, he says ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuEolubaAnN","text_ar":"ثُعْلُبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAmb, Msb:) or the former applies to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female"},{"kind":"text","text":"is called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaEolabapN","text_ar":"ثَعْلَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ks, S, Msb, K;) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male,"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuEolubaAnN","text_ar":"ثُعْلُبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaEolabN","text_ar":"ثَعْلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [accord. to some,] like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqorabapN","text_ar":"عَقْرَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqorubaAnN","text_ar":"عُقْرُبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqorabN","text_ar":"عَقْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaEolabN","text_ar":"ثَعْلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female"},{"kind":"text","text":"is called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuEaAlapu","text_ar":"ثُعَالَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Az, TA: [but see this word is art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vEl","text_ar":"ثعل"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vElb","text_ar":"ثعلب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaEaAlibu","text_ar":"ثَعَالِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaEaAlK","text_ar":"ثَعَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) accord. to Lh: but ISd disapproves of this [latter pl.]; and Sb does not allow it except in poetry. (TA.) F charges J with error in citing, as a proof that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuEolubaAnN","text_ar":"ثُعْلُبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the following verse:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^arab~N yabuwlu Alv~uEolubaAnu biraA^osihi\n                      \n                     \n                        laqado *al~a mano baAlato Ealayohi Alv~aEaAlibu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Is he a Lord, upon whose head the he-fox makes water?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brA^sh","text_ar":"براسه"},{"kind":"text","text":"being syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the Mughnee, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":":)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vile indeed is he upon whom the foxes make water!"},{"kind":"text","text":"] said by a man who was keeper of an idol, on seeing a he-fox make water upon it: but in this, F opposes also Ks and others; and it is asserted by several authorities that the correct reading of the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vElbAn","text_ar":"ثعلبان"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a trad. whereby F attempts to establish his charge against J is not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaEolabaAni","text_ar":"ثَعْلَبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", dual. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaEolabN","text_ar":"ثَعْلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as he pronounces it to be, but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuEolabaAni","text_ar":"ثُعْلَبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is said to be the masc. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaEolabN","text_ar":"ثَعْلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ufoEuwaAnN","text_ar":"اُفْعُوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqorubaAnN","text_ar":"عُقْرُبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are mascs. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEFY","text_ar":"اَفْعًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqorabN","text_ar":"عَقْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daA='u Alv~aEolabi","text_ar":"دَا=ءُ الثَّعْلَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for which Golius seems to have found in a copy of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawaA='u Alv~aEolabi","text_ar":"دَوَا=ءُ الثَّعْلَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well-known disease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alopecia,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in consequence of which the hair falls off."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einabu Alv~aEolabi","text_ar":"عِنَبُ الثَّعْلَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fox-grape:"},{"kind":"text","text":"rendered by Golius “"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uvæ vulpinæ,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"solanum:"},{"kind":"text","text":"” but now applied by some to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gooseberry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the solanum nigrum, or gardennightshade, is now commonly called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einabu Al*~iy^obi","text_ar":"عِنَبُ الذِّيْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain astringent, cooling plant: seven"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or, as in one copy of the K,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nine"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~aAt","text_ar":"حَبَّات"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which here seems to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"berries] thereof, swallowed, are a cure for the jaundice"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlyaraqaAn","text_ar":"اليَرَقَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and stop pregnancy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the berries of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xirowaE","text_ar":"خِرْوَع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"castor-oil-plant], for the year, or, as some say, absolutely."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hole,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aperture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juHor","text_ar":"جُحْر"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whence rain-water flows."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [And particularly,] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outlet, hole,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aperture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxoraj","text_ar":"مَخْرَج"},{"kind":"text","text":", S and Msb, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juHor","text_ar":"جُحْر"},{"kind":"text","text":", K, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaqob","text_ar":"ثَقْب"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whence the rain-water flows from the place where dates are dried."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA.) And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place whence the water flows forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, [probably a mistake,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a watering-trough"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tank."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.)       -A3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper extremity of a spear-shaft that enters into the head thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest part of a palm-shoot when it is cut from [the root of] the mother-tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest part of a [shoot such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rAkuwb","text_ar":"راكُوب"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the trunk of a palm-tree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","IAmb","Msb","Ks","TA","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}